<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[848,1491,410,497]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[848,987,410,434]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[848,958,410,434]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
First flagellomere 1.2 times as long as wide. Fore coxa yellow, mid and hind coxae brownish. Dorsal lobe of surstyli with plumose hair.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[848,1491,538,593]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[848,1068,538,562]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[848,975,538,562]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Description</emphasis>
. – Male
</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[1220,1352,538,561]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.7 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[848,981,570,593]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="2.35" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[848,1491,634,881]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
Head metallic green with pale grey pollen. Face narrowing downward, narrower than first flagellomere. Hairs and bristles black. Postocular bristles (including posteroventral hairs) black. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1100,730,753]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="10.[148,192,2107,2128]" captionTargetBox="[153,1480,966,2063]" captionTargetId="figure-26@10.[137,1505,943,2087]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs. 29–32. Hercostomus plumatus, new species, male: 29, antenna; 30, male genitalia; 31, cercus; 32, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339243/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) brownish; first flagellomere darker, 1.2 times as long as wide; arista dark brown, minutely pubescent with short basal segment. Proboscis brownish yellow with black hairs, palpus brownish yellow with black hairs and black apical bristle.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339243" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5339243" box="[148,1250,2107,2128]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339243/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" startId="10.[148,192,2107,2128]" targetBox="[153,1480,966,2063]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph blockId="10.[148,1250,2107,2128]" box="[148,1250,2107,2128]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
Figs. 29–32. 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[277,499,2107,2128]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plumatus" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[277,499,2107,2128]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Hercostomus plumatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[513,633,2107,2128]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male: 29, antenna; 30, male genitalia; 31, cercus; 32, surstyli.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="11.[126,765,206,709]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Thorax metallic green with pale grey pollen. Six strong dc, 5–6 pairs of acr; scutellum with two pairs of bristles (basal pair short and weak). Propleuron with 1 black bristle on lower part. Legs yellow; fore coxa yellow, mid and hind coxae brownish. Mid and hind tarsi from tip of tarsomere 1 onward brownish to brown. Hairs and bristles black. Mid and hind coxae each with 1 exterior bristle. Mid and hind femora each with 1 preapical bristle. Fore tibia with 2 ad and 1 weak pd, apically with 3 bristles; mid tibia with 3 ad, 2 pd and 1 av, apically with 4 bristles; hind tibia with 4 ad, 3 pd and 2 vs., apically with 3 bristles. Relative lengths of tibia and 5 tarsomeres LI 1.0: 0.5: 0.2: 0.15: 0.15: 0.15; LII 1.5: 0.65: 0.4: 0.3: 0.2: 0.2; LIII 1.65: 0.5: 0.7: 0.5: 0.35: 0.25. Wing hyaline, tinged with greyish, veins brown; CuAx ratio 0.9, R4+5 and M parallel apically. Squama yellow with black hairs. Halter yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[126,765,750,901]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
Abdomen metallic green with pale grey pollen. Hairs and bristles black. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[434,562,782,805]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="10.[148,192,2107,2128]" captionTargetBox="[153,1480,966,2063]" captionTargetId="figure-26@10.[137,1505,943,2087]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs. 29–32. Hercostomus plumatus, new species, male: 29, antenna; 30, male genitalia; 31, cercus; 32, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5339243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5339243/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Figs. 30–32</figureCitation>
): Epandrium longer than wide, lateral epandrial lobe slightly curved apically with 3 bristles; cercus nearly triangular; hypandrium narrow and straight; aedeagus with 1 minute, inner denticle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[126,765,941,997]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[126,216,941,965]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[361,445,942,965]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[591,676,942,965]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
. Similar to male, but fore tibia without weak pd.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="28" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[126,764,1037,1093]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[126,271,1037,1061]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[126,243,1037,1061]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Etymology</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the plumose hair on the dorsal lobe of surstyli.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
