<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[126,766,1197,1349]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[126,257,1197,1221]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[126,226,1197,1221]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" status="new species">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">H. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[257,385,1230,1253]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but may be separated from the latter by its triangular cercus and aedeagus with 1 inner denticle; in 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2008" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2008" box="[153,306,1294,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[153,306,1294,1317]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">H. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[320,451,1294,1317]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the cercus is strongly curved and nearly geniculate and the aedeagus has 2 inner denticles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
